A: The problem is that you are not sending a line break after each write. The BufferedReader reads until it finds a line break, so it reads "123" as one line.
You should use printWriter.println("1"); instead of printWriter.write("1"); for each line. This will add a line break after each line.
Here is the corrected code:
PrintWriter printWriter = ...
printWriter.println("1");
printWriter.println("2");
printWriter.println("3");

And then you can read the lines with:
ServerSocket serverSocket = ...
Socket socket = serverSocket.accept();
BufferedReader bufferedReader = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(socket.getInputStream()));
String line;
while ((line = bufferedReader.readLine()) != null) {
    System.out.println(line);
}

This will print each line separately.

